---

<PageShell
  title="Austria Investor Visa 2026: Red-White-Red Card, Requirements & Insurance Guide"
  description="Complete guide to Austria's investor and entrepreneur visas. Red-White-Red Card for self-employed, start-up founders, and investors. Insurance requirements and path to permanent residence."
  headline="Austria Investor Visa: Red-White-Red Card Guide"
  subheadline="Everything you need to know about Austria's entrepreneur and investor residence permits—including the Red-White-Red Card for self-employed, start-up visa, and paths to permanent residence in the heart of Europe."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Premium Insurance"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/allianz-care"
  heroImage="/images/countries/austria-hero-bg.png"
>

  <!-- Trust Signals -->
  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-8 text-sm text-neutral-600">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Updated February 2026
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Official Austrian Requirements
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      €50,000+ Investment Path
    </span>
  </div>

  <!-- Section: Overview -->
  <section id="overview" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Austria offers several pathways for investors and entrepreneurs to obtain residence through its Red-White-Red Card system. While Austria doesn't have a classic "Golden Visa" program with a fixed real estate investment threshold, it provides merit-based options for self-employed professionals, start-up founders, and significant investors who contribute to the Austrian economy.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The Austrian approach combines economic benefit assessment with a points-based system for certain categories. Whether you're launching an innovative start-up in Vienna's tech scene, establishing a traditional business, or making a substantial investment, Austria offers pathways to residence—and eventually citizenship—in one of Europe's most livable countries.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts: Austria Investor/Entrepreneur Visa</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-primary-800">
        <li>• <strong>Main pathway:</strong> Red-White-Red Card for Self-Employed Key Workers</li>
        <li>• <strong>Minimum investment:</strong> €50,000+ with proven economic benefit</li>
        <li>• <strong>Start-up visa:</strong> 2-year permit for innovative business founders</li>
        <li>• <strong>Duration:</strong> 1-2 years initial, renewable</li>
        <li>• <strong>Family included:</strong> Spouse and minor children eligible</li>
        <li>• <strong>Path to PR:</strong> 5 years of legal residence</li>
        <li>• <strong>Path to citizenship:</strong> 10 years (6 with integration achievements)</li>
        <li>• <strong>EU benefits:</strong> Schengen travel, access to Austrian healthcare</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Why Choose Austria?</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Advantages</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• Exceptional quality of life (Vienna ranks #1 globally)</li>
          <li>• Central European location—gateway to East and West</li>
          <li>• Strong economy with low unemployment</li>
          <li>• Excellent education and healthcare systems</li>
          <li>• German-speaking EU country (business language)</li>
          <li>• Rich cultural scene and outdoor lifestyle</li>
          <li>• Lower cost than Switzerland, similar benefits</li>
          <li>• Stable political and economic environment</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>• No straightforward real estate investment visa</li>
          <li>• Must demonstrate economic benefit to Austria</li>
          <li>• German increasingly important for integration</li>
          <li>• Longer path to citizenship (10 years standard)</li>
          <li>• Dual citizenship generally not allowed</li>
          <li>• Bureaucracy can be thorough</li>
          <li>• Higher taxes than some alternatives</li>
          <li>• Limited annual quotas for some visa types</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Vienna advantage:</strong> Vienna has been ranked the world's most livable city for years running. For entrepreneurs, it offers a growing tech ecosystem, excellent infrastructure, and a strategic location bridging Western and Central/Eastern European markets. The city is also increasingly English-friendly in business contexts.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Quick Decision Guide -->
  <section id="quick-decision" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Quick Decision Guide</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Austria's Investor Visa is Right For You If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• You want Europe's highest quality of life</li>
          <li>• You value German-speaking business environment</li>
          <li>• You're building an innovative start-up</li>
          <li>• You have specialized skills/qualifications</li>
          <li>• You want central European location</li>
          <li>• You prefer lower costs than Switzerland</li>
          <li>• You're comfortable with 10-year citizenship path</li>
          <li>• You appreciate culture, arts, and outdoor activities</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Other Options If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>• You want a passive real estate investment visa</li>
          <li>• You need a clear, fixed investment threshold</li>
          <li>• You want faster citizenship (Portugal: 5 years)</li>
          <li>• You require dual citizenship</li>
          <li>• You prefer English-only business environment</li>
          <li>• You want minimal physical presence requirements</li>
          <li>• You prioritize tax optimization</li>
          <li>• You prefer Mediterranean climate</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Austria vs. Other EU Options</h3>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
          <tr>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Country</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Program Type</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Min. Investment</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Citizenship Path</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Austria</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">RWR Card (Self-Employed)</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">€50,000+ (merit-based)</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">10 years (6 accelerated)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-neutral-50">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Germany</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Entrepreneur Visa</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">None (merit-based)</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">8 years (6 accelerated)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Switzerland</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Lump-Sum Taxation</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">CHF 400K+ annual tax</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">12 years</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-neutral-50">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Portugal</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Golden Visa</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">€500,000 (funds)</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">5 years</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Why Austria stands out:</strong> Austria offers the best quality of life in Europe at a lower cost than Switzerland, with similar benefits. For entrepreneurs who value stability, culture, and a central European base, Austria provides excellent infrastructure and market access—though the path to citizenship is longer than southern European alternatives.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Investment Requirements -->
  <section id="investment-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Investment Requirements</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Austria offers several pathways for entrepreneurs and investors, each with different requirements. Unlike Golden Visa programs with fixed real estate thresholds, Austria evaluates applications based on economic benefit, innovation potential, and your qualifications.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={requirementsColumns} rows={requirementsRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Red-White-Red Card Categories</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Self-Employed Key Workers (Selbständige Schlüsselkräfte)</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The main pathway for entrepreneurs. Requires minimum €50,000 investment and demonstrated economic benefit. You must show transfer of investment capital, creation of jobs, and/or introduction of new technologies or services. A positive assessment from the Austrian Economic Chamber (WKO) is typically required.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Start-up Founder Visa</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">For innovative business founders with backing from an approved incubator, accelerator, or investor. Must develop an innovative product, service, or business model. Initial 2-year permit, renewable. Best suited for tech entrepreneurs and those with novel business concepts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Settlement Permit for Major Investors</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">For significant investors who create substantial economic benefit. No fixed minimum, but typically involves major investments creating multiple jobs. Grants immediate settlement permit rather than temporary residence. Requires positive assessment from ABA (Austrian Business Agency).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Artists and Athletes</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Special pathway for individuals with exceptional cultural or athletic achievements. Simplified process for those who can demonstrate significant cultural contribution or international recognition. Assessed on individual merit.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Self-Employed Key Worker Requirements</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Financial Requirements</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• <strong>Minimum investment:</strong> €50,000</li>
          <li>• Must be transferred to Austrian business</li>
          <li>• Proof of investment origin required</li>
          <li>• Sufficient funds for living expenses</li>
          <li>• ~€1,200/month personal resources</li>
          <li>• Additional funds for dependents</li>
          <li>• Clean financial background</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Economic Benefit Criteria</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• Creates new jobs in Austria</li>
          <li>• Transfers new technology or knowledge</li>
          <li>• Export potential or foreign investment</li>
          <li>• Fills a market gap or need</li>
          <li>• Comparable or additional to existing services</li>
          <li>• Contributes to Austrian economy</li>
          <li>• WKO positive assessment required</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Points-Based Assessment (Where Applicable)</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Some Austrian visa categories use a points system. While the Self-Employed Key Worker category focuses on economic benefit, understanding the points framework helps with applications:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Qualifications:</strong> University degrees, especially Austrian/EEA recognized</li>
      <li><strong>Work experience:</strong> Years of relevant professional experience</li>
      <li><strong>Language skills:</strong> German (A1-B2) and/or English proficiency</li>
      <li><strong>Age:</strong> Younger applicants score higher (under 30 maximum points)</li>
      <li><strong>Austria connection:</strong> Previous study or work in Austria</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-amber-800">
        <strong>Important:</strong> Austria has annual quotas for certain residence permit categories. The Self-Employed Key Worker category is not subject to quotas, but applications are processed on a first-come basis. Apply early in the year if possible and ensure your documentation is complete.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Insurance Requirements -->
  <section id="insurance-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2">Health Insurance is Mandatory</h3>
      <p class="text-green-800">
        Austria requires proof of comprehensive health insurance for all residence permit applications. Your coverage must be valid in Austria and cover the full duration of your permit. Once your business is established and generating income, you'll be enrolled in Austria's social insurance system.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Austria has a two-tier healthcare system: mandatory social insurance (ÖGK) for employed and self-employed individuals earning above a threshold, and private insurance options. For your initial visa application, you'll typically use international private insurance, then transition to Austrian social or private insurance once established.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={insuranceColumns} rows={insuranceRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Insurance Options for Entrepreneurs</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Austrian Social Insurance (SVS)</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
          <li>• Mandatory once self-employed income exceeds threshold</li>
          <li>• Premium: ~20% of income (pension, health, accident)</li>
          <li>• Comprehensive Austrian healthcare coverage</li>
          <li>• Pension contributions included</li>
          <li>• Family members can be co-insured</li>
          <li>• Some out-of-pocket costs for treatments</li>
          <li>• Optional supplementary private insurance available</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">International Private Insurance</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• Essential for initial visa application</li>
          <li>• Continues as supplement or alternative</li>
          <li>• €80-400/month depending on coverage</li>
          <li>• Global coverage for frequent travelers</li>
          <li>• Faster access to specialists</li>
          <li>• Choice of private hospitals</li>
          <li>• Portable if you relocate</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Insurance Timeline for Entrepreneurs</h3>

    <div class="space-y-4 mb-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Phase 1: Visa Application</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">For your RWR Card application, you need private health insurance covering Austria. International providers like Allianz Care, Cigna Global, or DR-WALTER explicitly meet Austrian visa requirements. Budget €80-200/month.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Phase 2: Business Establishment</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Once you register your business with the Gewerbebehörde and start earning income, you'll be enrolled in the SVS (Sozialversicherung der Selbständigen). This happens automatically when you register your trade. Continue private insurance as supplement if desired.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Phase 3: Ongoing Coverage</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Most entrepreneurs maintain Austrian social insurance (mandatory above income thresholds) plus optional private supplementary insurance for faster appointments, private rooms, and broader coverage. International insurance remains valuable for frequent travelers.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Visa application tip:</strong> For your RWR Card application, use established international insurers that explicitly state Austria compliance. Allianz Care and DR-WALTER are commonly accepted. Ensure your policy letter clearly states coverage in Austria, minimum €30,000 medical coverage, and the full visa duration.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Box -->
  <CTABox
    variant="highlight"
    title="Need insurance for your Austria Investor Visa?"
    description="Compare international insurers that meet Austrian visa requirements."
    buttonText="Compare Premium Insurance"
    buttonHref="/go/allianz-care"
  />

  <!-- Section: Recommended Providers -->
  <section id="recommended-providers" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      For your Austrian investor visa, you'll need insurance that's recognized by Austrian authorities. Here are the best options for different stages and situations:
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Provider Recommendations by Situation</h3>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Visa Application Phase</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Allianz Care or DR-WALTER are reliable choices for the initial visa application. Both explicitly meet Austrian requirements and issue clear documentation. Budget €80-200/month for comprehensive coverage.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Established Entrepreneur (Vienna-Based)</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Once enrolled in SVS, consider adding UNIQA or another Austrian private insurer as supplement. This gives you faster access to specialists and private hospital rooms while maintaining your social insurance coverage.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Frequent International Traveler</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Cigna Global or Allianz Care work well as primary or supplementary coverage if you travel frequently. These provide seamless worldwide coverage and don't require you to return to Austria for treatment. Budget €200-400/month.</p>
