  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The Austrian RWR Card application involves multiple steps and typically takes 2-4 months from submission to approval. Applications are processed by the provincial immigration authority (MA 35 in Vienna) with input from the Austrian Economic Chamber (WKO) and labor market service (AMS).
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={timelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Step-by-Step Guide</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Prepare Your Business Plan and Documentation</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Develop a comprehensive business plan showing economic benefit to Austria. Gather supporting documents: passport, educational certificates, work experience proof, criminal record certificate, health insurance, and proof of €50,000+ investment capital. Documents may need apostilles and certified German translations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Submit Application at Austrian Embassy</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Book an appointment at your local Austrian embassy or consulate. Submit your complete application with all documents. Pay the visa fee (€160). The embassy forwards your application to Austria for processing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">WKO and AMS Assessment</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">The Austrian Economic Chamber (WKO) evaluates the economic benefit of your business. The labor market service (AMS) assesses labor market impact. Both provide opinions to the immigration authority. This process takes 2-4 weeks.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Immigration Authority Review</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">The provincial immigration authority (MA 35 in Vienna, other offices in other provinces) reviews your complete application. They may request additional documents or clarification. Processing takes 4-8 weeks after receiving all assessments.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Visa Issuance and Entry</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Upon approval, the embassy issues your entry visa. Enter Austria within the visa validity period (usually 90 days). You can start setting up your business immediately upon arrival.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">6</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Register Residence (Meldezettel)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Within 3 days of finding accommodation, register your residence at the local Meldeamt (registration office). Bring your passport, rental agreement, and completed registration form. The Meldezettel is required for all subsequent administrative steps.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">7</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Collect Biometric Residence Permit</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Schedule an appointment with MA 35 (or your provincial immigration authority) to provide biometrics and collect your RWR Card. This is a physical card valid for 1-2 years, renewable. Bring your passport and Meldezettel.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">8</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Register Your Business</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Register with the Gewerbebehörde (trade authority) for your Gewerbeschein (trade license). For a GmbH, complete notarization and register with the Firmenbuch (commercial register). Register with the tax office (Finanzamt) and open an Austrian business bank account.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Vienna-specific tip:</strong> Vienna's MA 35 handles a high volume of applications. Book appointments early (they fill up weeks in advance), arrive with complete documentation, and consider working with an immigration lawyer who has established relationships with the office. The Vienna Business Agency also offers free support for international entrepreneurs.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Real-World Scenarios -->
  <section id="scenarios" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

    <p class="mb-6">
      Here's how different situations typically play out for investor and entrepreneur visa applicants in Austria:
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
